folder: Carmine Street & Bedford Street, Manhattan, NY
text:

51-59 Carmine Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Bedford Street.

March 8, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

The same four buildings after drastic alterations. This view also shows the west side of Bedford Street all the way to Leroy Street and Seventh Avenue South.

March 27, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Carmine Street & Bedford Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
1. Carmine Street, north from Bedford Street. Before Seventh Avenue South was cut in 1915, Carmine Street was the connecting link between the northern end of Varick Street and the southern end of Sixth Avenue. At one time the Varick Street surface line continued over Carmine Street to and up Sixth Avenue.
April 3, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

2. Carmine St., n.e., from Bedford St. Neg. A-111
P.L. Sperr, photographer
May 14, 1941
